@NODE "FadeMusicDown()" "Music: FadeMusicDown()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     FadeMusicDown()
Short:    Fade the music down to a certain volume.
Synopsis: LONG FadeMusicDown(*Music [a0], LONG FadeState [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Use  this function to achieve fading effects for your music.  To fade music
down to nothing, use a loop-back routine like this:

  State = NULL;
  while (State = FadeMusicDown(Music, State)) {
    /* Do whatever you like in here */
  }

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Music
  Pointer to a Music object.

FadeState
  Should set to NULL if you want to begin with the current volume, or set
  to Music->Volume if that is more suitable for you.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Music: @{"FadeMusicUp()" LINK "FadeMusicUp()"}

@EndNode
