@NODE "FadeMusicUp()" "Music: FadeMusicUp()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     FadeMusicUp()
Short:    Fade the music up to a certain volume.
Synopsis: LONG FadeMusicUp(*Music [a0], LONG FadeState [d0])

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
Use  this function to achieve fading effects for your music.  To fade music
from nothing to 50%, use a loop-back routine like this:

  State = Music->Volume;
  while ((State = FadeMusicUp(Music, State)) < 50) {
    /* Do whatever you like in here */
  }

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Music
  Pointer to a Music object.

FadeState
  Should set to NULL if you want to begin with the current volume, or set
  to Music->Volume if that is more suitable for you.

@{b}@{u}SEE ALSO@{uu}@{ub}
Music: @{"FadeMusicDown()" LINK "FadeMusicDown()"}

@EndNode
