@NODE "SetMusicChannel()" "Music: SetMusicChannel()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     SetMusicChannel()
Short:    LONG SetMusicChannel(*Music [a0], WORD Channel [d0],
            WORD Setting [d1])
Synopsis: Turn a particular music channel on or off.

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
If you are aware of the instrumental arrangement of a music module, you can
turn  channels  on/off  for certain effects.  You might get the musician to
use  Channel  1  for  drums, 2 for guitars, 3 for vocals etc.  Then you can
alter the channels with the knowledge of what you are changing.

@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}
This function does not impact upon Sound objects.

@{b}@{u}INPUT@{uu}@{ub}
Music
  Pointer to a Music object.

Channel
  The channel number that you want to alter.

Setting
  Use TRUE (1) for "on" and FALSE (0) for "off".

@{b}@{u}RESULT@{uu}@{ub}
Returns ERR_OK if successful.

@EndNode
